    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>White veils, often lace or embroidered, used in the Christian baptism or christening ceremony to cover the head of the baptized or christened adult or child.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
